## Core Viability Assessment
Verdict: Viable long-term passive income project for a developer. Competitor traffic data (Calcul Conversion 476K–610K monthly visits) confirms real sustained demand. B2B audience commands premium ad CPM rates ($15–$35+). Zero operational cost infrastructure is legitimate and well-architected. However monetization timeline and competitive positioning claims in the source documents are optimistic and should be treated skeptically.

## Key Issues Identified

### 1. AdSense vs. Clean UX Contradiction
Documents simultaneously pitch a clean ad-free experience as the competitive edge while requiring Google AdSense for revenue. These goals are mutually exclusive at launch. Auto Ads inject dynamic banners that destroy the speed and UX advantage over Calcul Conversion.

### 2. Quebec Law 25 Compliance Complexity
Cookie-free Plausible Analytics does not exempt the site from consent requirements once AdSense is active. Google drops behavioral tracking cookies the moment AdSense loads, triggering Quebec Law 25 opt-in consent requirements. A certified CMP banner adds friction that undermines the clean UX positioning.

### 3. AdSense Approval Barrier
A single-page calculator will be rejected by Google AdSense for low value content. Provincial sub-pages are mandatory before monetization is even possible, substantially increasing actual build scope beyond what the documents imply.

### 4. SEO Timeline Underestimated
Competing against Canada.ca institutional authority, Calcul Conversion's established domain age, and iBill's enterprise backing realistically requires 12–24 months of SEO runway before meaningful organic traffic. The documents present this as a faster process than it is.

### 5. Automation Layer Fragility
The GitHub Actions HTML scraper targeting the Retail Council website is brittle. CSS class changes, structural redesigns, or Cloudflare bot protection on the target site will cause silent failures or false alerts.

## All Recommendations

### Monetization
- Delay AdSense — launch ad-free, build domain authority for 6–12 months, then introduce manually placed static ad units in fixed positions rather than Auto Ads
- Pursue affiliate marketing instead of or before AdSense — single affiliate relationship with Wave, FreshBooks, or QuickBooks will generate more predictable revenue than AdSense at early traffic volumes without the Quebec Law 25 complications
- Contextual affiliate placement: text link beneath ITC output results panel, not a banner

### Privacy and Legal
- Use Plausible Analytics exclusively for cookieless tracking — no consent banner required for analytics alone
- If AdSense is eventually added, geofence the CMP consent banner to Quebec visitors only using Cloudflare Workers — preserves UX for majority of non-Quebec traffic
- Gate only AdSense behind CMP, not the entire page
- Add explicit PIPEDA compliance language to the privacy page covering all Canadian users not just Quebec
- Retain the accounting disclaimer adjacent to the calculate button as documented

### SEO and Content Phasing
- Phase 1 Ontario and Quebec only — highest population, highest search volume, most competitive differentiation opportunity
- Phase 2 BC, Alberta, Nova Scotia
- Phase 3 remaining provinces, historical rate pages, status card exemption content
- Build historical audit keyword pages (e.g. /history/ontario-2024/) for zero-competition long-tail traffic
- Embed FinancialProduct and FAQPage JSON-LD schemas from day one

### Automation
- Replace the daily Retail Council HTML scraper with a manual quarterly review — Canadian tax rates change at most once annually at budget time
- Repurpose GitHub Actions cron to run Vitest and Playwright test suite instead
- Set a free Google Alert for "GST HST rate change" as the early warning system
- Replace Discord webhook infrastructure with the Google Alert for simplicity at this stage

### Security Additions Not Covered in Documents
- Add Subresource Integrity (SRI) hashing to all third-party CDN scripts
- Explicitly sanitize URL parameter inputs before any DOM interaction — likely attack vector if shareable calculation URLs are implemented
- Add quarterly npm audit to GitHub Actions workflow for axios and cheerio dependencies
- Add request throttling and crawl delays to the verify-rates.js scraper
- Establish a Discord webhook rotation procedure — treat it as a rotatable secret, rotate quarterly or immediately if exposed in build logs
- Enable Cloudflare Bot Fight Mode, verify DDoS protection is active, enable Cloudflare WAF free tier

### Build Scope Reduction
- Build and deploy MVP first — domain age starts counting on launch day not planning day
- Keep MVP to a single HTML file, Ontario and Quebec only

