### Stage 4 — Scale and Optimization
Timeline: Month 6–12
- Add remaining provinces and territories
- Build Receipt Stack batch processor with CSV export
- Add ITC Apportionment Slider
- Implement historical rate sub-pages for prior fiscal years
- Evaluate Ezoic or Mediavine header bidding if monthly traffic exceeds 10,000 page views
- Quarterly manual tax rate verification against CRA
- Quarterly npm audit run
- Quarterly Discord webhook rotation if applicable
- Review and update VERIFIED_TIMESTAMP in taxRates.js after each verification

## Critical Path Items in Priority Order
1. Launch MVP — nothing else starts the clock on domain age and SEO
2. Apply to Wave affiliate — 4–8 weeks post-launch
3. Build provincial sub-pages — prerequisite for AdSense approval
4. Add URL parameter sanitization — before any shareable URL feature
5. SRI hashing — before any third-party scripts are added
6. Geofenced CMP — before AdSense is ever activated

## What This Project Is and Is Not
It is: A sound long-term passive income project for a developer with realistic 12–18 month horizon to meaningful revenue.
It is not: A fast monetization opportunity. Anyone expecting significant ad revenue within the first 6 months should recalibrate expectations. Domain age, content volume, and organic traffic accumulation are time-dependent variables that no amount of technical optimization can shortcut.